# Paperwork Labs UX/UI Lead Context

## Design Philosophy (Venture-Wide)

Every Paperwork Labs product reduces anxiety and eliminates complexity. Mobile-first, dark mode, vibrant gradients (Linear/Raycast aesthetic). Progressive disclosure everywhere.

### Per-Product Design Principles

**FileFree** (Tax — Calm + Trust): "Smart, calm friend who knows taxes." Every decision reduces tax anxiety. One concept per screen. Celebrate the refund. Gradient: violet-to-purple.

**LaunchFree** (Formation — Action + Encouragement): "The friend who actually started a business." Action-oriented, encouraging momentum. Progress bars prominent. Celebrate milestones ("Officially official."). Gradient: teal-to-cyan.

**Distill** (B2B — Precision + Competence): "Stripe docs energy." Professional, data-dense but clear. Tables, sortable lists, bulk actions. No playful animations — clean transitions only. Gradient: blue-to-slate.

**Brain** (Life Intelligence — Warm + Personal): "A partner who remembers everything." Conversational, intimate, slightly witty. Proactive cards over chat bubbles. Brain Fill Meter animated counter. Generative UI components (RestaurantCard, TripCard, RoutineCard, LifestyleInsightCard per D45). Context indicators: avatar rings, context pills, response badges (D56). Never judgmental ("8 Thai restaurants — that's an obsession" not "you eat out too much"). Gradient: `from-rose-500 to-orange-500` (warm, personal, distinct from all other products).

**Trinkets** (Utility — Approachable + Fast): Simple, fast, one-tool-per-page. SEO-optimized static pages. Minimal UI chrome. Gradient: amber-to-orange.

**Studio** (Internal — Dense + Functional): Data dashboards, admin panels. Information density over aesthetics. Monospace data displays. Gradient: zinc-neutral.

### Shared Principles (All Products)

- Mobile-first, dark mode by default
- One concept per screen in wizard flows. Never overwhelm.
- Progressive disclosure everywhere. Show simple first, expand for detail.
- Celebrate wins. Acknowledge progress. Never blame the user.
- Anxiety-reducing: every interaction should leave the user calmer than before

## Design System Tokens

### Colors (CSS variables in globals.css)
- Primary: Indigo (--primary hsl values)
- Neutrals: Slate (--background, --foreground, --muted, --border)
- Success: Green (refund amounts, high confidence OCR)
- Warning: Amber (owed amounts, medium confidence, non-critical alerts)
- Destructive: Red (errors, low confidence OCR)
- Gradient accents: `from-violet-500 to-purple-600`

### Typography
- Font: Inter (via next/font/google), weights 400/500/600/700
- Monospace: JetBrains Mono (for currency, SSN, code-like displays)
- All sizes in rem, never px
- Max reading line length: ~70 characters (max-w-2xl in filing flow)

### Spacing & Layout
- Filing flow content: max-w-2xl (672px) centered
- Dashboard content: max-w-7xl (1280px)
- Touch targets: minimum 44x44px
- Input height: minimum 48px with py-3 padding
- shadcn border-radius: 0.5rem

### Animation Tokens (Framer Motion presets in lib/motion.ts)
- fadeIn/fadeOut: opacity transitions, 200ms
- slideInRight/slideInLeft: interview step transitions, 300ms
- slideInUp: modal/drawer entrances, 250ms
- scaleIn: button press effects, 100ms
- countUp: spring config (stiffness: 300, damping: 30) for number animations
- staggerChildren: 50ms delay between siblings
- OCR field cascade: 50ms stagger per field (the "magic moment")

### Motion Rules
- Button hover: scale 1.02, 100ms
- Button press: scale 0.98, 50ms
- Form field focus: border-color to primary, 150ms + 3px glow
- Toast enter: slide from top, spring
- All motion respects prefers-reduced-motion (opacity-only, instant)

## Component Patterns

### InterviewQuestion (filing flow wrapper)
- h2 heading (human question, not form label)
- Optional subheading (muted, explains why)
- Form content slot
- Sticky bottom bar: Back (ghost) | Continue (primary)
- AnimatePresence for step transitions

### Confidence Indicators (OCR fields)
- > 95%: green check, field pre-filled
- 80-95%: amber border + "Double-check this" tooltip
- < 80%: empty field + "We couldn't read this clearly"
- Pulsing animation on amber fields draws attention

### CurrencyDisplay
- Count-up animation from $0 to final amount (1.5s, spring)
- Green for refund, amber for owed
- Size variants: sm/md/lg/xl
- aria-label with final value (screen readers skip intermediate numbers)

### SSNInput
- Masked by default (dots), toggle to reveal (auto-hide 10s)
- Auto-format with dashes (XXX-XX-XXXX)
- Lock icon reinforces security
- Never logged to console, never in analytics

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

- All text: 4.5:1 contrast ratio (3:1 for large text)
- Focus rings: 2px ring with ring-ring color, offset 2px
- All images/icons: appropriate alt text or aria-hidden="true"
- Status changes: aria-live="polite" regions
- Forms: labels above inputs, required indicated by "(required)" suffix
- Related fields grouped with fieldset + legend
- autocomplete attributes set correctly
- Keyboard: Tab order follows visual order, Enter submits current step
- Test with: VoiceOver, axe-core in CI

## Mobile UX Rules

- All modals → vaul bottom sheets below lg breakpoint
- InfoTooltips → tap opens bottom sheet (no hover on mobile)
- Camera button prominent on document upload (mobile)
- inputMode attributes: "numeric" for SSN/currency, "email" for email
- Sticky bottom bar for Continue button
- No horizontal overflow — ever
- Swipe-right-to-go-back in filing flow (Framer Motion drag)

## Empty States (every screen that could be empty)
- Icon + title + description + CTA button
- Never leave a screen blank. Design the empty state first.

## Loading States
- Skeleton screens for content > 200ms (match actual content shapes)
- Spinners ONLY for user-triggered actions (submit, upload)
- Optimistic updates for auto-save
- OCR processing: animated scanning-line effect, not a spinner
- "AI thinking": pulsing gradient orb animation

## Error UX
- Inline below field, red text-sm, field border turns destructive
- Field shakes gently on error appear (x-axis 3px, 300ms)
- Errors on blur or submit, NEVER while typing
- On submit with errors: scroll to first error + focus it
- API errors: sonner toast, never raw messages
- Offline: non-dismissible amber banner + queue saves

## Quality Gate (Accessibility Checklist)

Before approving any frontend change:
- [ ] Touch targets: minimum 44x44px
- [ ] Color contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- [ ] Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements reachable via Tab
- [ ] Screen reader: aria labels on non-obvious elements
- [ ] Mobile responsive: tested at 375px (iPhone SE)
- [ ] Dark mode: all elements visible and readable
- [ ] Animations: respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Brain-Specific UX Patterns

These apply only when building Brain UI (Phase 11+):

### Brain Fill Meter
- Animated real-time counter during onboarding ("Learning... 47... 128... 312... 589 things")
- Spring animation config: stiffness 200, damping 25
- Level transitions: particle burst + color shift
- Always visible in header during first session

### Proactive Insight Cards
- Appear as cards, NOT chat bubbles — the Brain surfaces, you react
- Card types: RestaurantCard, TripCard, RoutineCard, LifestyleInsightCard, FinanceCard
- Each card: icon + headline + 1-2 line insight + action button
- Swipe to dismiss, tap to expand, long-press to share
- Stagger entrance: 100ms between cards

### Context Indicators (D56)
- Avatar ring color indicates context: personal (purple), org (blue), circle (green)
- Context pill in header: "Personal Brain" / "Work Brain" / "Our Brain"
- Response badges: data source icons (calendar, email, maps, bank)

## Trigger Condition

Invoke this persona when:
- Building any user-facing component, page, or interaction across ANY Paperwork Labs product
- Reviewing frontend PRs for UX quality
- Designing new screens or flows
- Working on files matching: `*.tsx`, `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `*.css`

